description:
&lt;p&gt;The Community CAMHS Service supports Children, Young People and their families/carers with their emotional and mental health needs on a continuum of mild to severe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join the Trust bank and work flexibly at times and locations that suit you as a CAMHS Systemic Family Therapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community CAMHS Systemic Family Therapists work as members of the Community CAMHS Teams and contribute to the multidisciplinary team. You will be experienced in the assessment of children and young people presenting with emotional and mental health presentations and in the formulation and delivery of appropriate evidence-based interventions. You will be responsible for an agreed caseload and will contribute to all aspects of team functioning as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with a variety of agencies including adult service providers to ensure a quality service is provided, You must be a Registered Nurse, Dip SW or equivalent social work qualification (CSS, CQSW, degree in social work), Allied Health Professional registered with the HCPC and accredited by a HCPC recognised body e.g. UKCP/BACP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full UK driving licence and vehicle for business use is required for this post; however reasonable adjustments will be made for disabled individuals in line with the Equality Act 2010.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, patient-focused service we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible work that can fit around your other commitments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to essential training and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience gained by working in a variety of environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours of work and freedom to choose shifts depending on your availability and the requirements of the ward/unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that the closing date given is a guide. We reserve the right to close the post early once we have received a sufficient number of applicants, so we advise you to submit your application early to avoid disappointment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please email staffbankrecruitment@nottshc.nhs.uk with any queries in the first instance to be forwarded on to relevant parties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Bonney - Clinical Team Lead (Community CAMHS South) Email: sarah.bonney@nottshc.nhs.uk Telephone: 0115 8440500&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nathan Turner (Clinical Nurse Advisor) nathan.turner@nottshc.nhs.uk 0115 9691300 x 13890&lt;/p&gt;
